	Madonna addition    
	 London, March 17: Madonna hopes to adopt a second child from Malawi to join her son David Banda, she has disclosed, reports The Daily Telegraph.      
	 The 50-year-old singer is considering the new addition to her family despite her recent divorce from husband Guy Ritchie.      
	Many people  especially our Malawian friends  say that David should have a Malawian brother or sister, she told the countrys Nation newspaper. Its something I have been considering but would only do if I had the support of the Malawian people and the government.      
	Madonna was accused of circumventing the rules when she adopted David from an orphanage in 2006. The star said she was determined to teach David, three, about his homeland. His father still lives in Malawi, one of the worlds poorest nations.    
	Model mess    
	 New York (AP): Supermodel Tyra Banks, host and executive producer of Americas Next Top Model show, says auditions for the series will continue following the chaos that erupted at a casting call over the weekend. Panic ensued among hundreds of people waiting to audition for the show on Saturday outside a hotel in Manhattan, resulting in three arrests and six injuries. The scene caused such a commotion that the street outside the hotel became littered with shoes and clothing.
                                                                                                                                                                       
